The paper deals with the design of robust transceivers for MIMO relay systems, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of Tomlinson-Harashima precoding (THP) and linear minimum-mean-squared-error (MMSE) receiver also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the signal processing (cs.SI) or multimedia (cs.MM) categories. Finally, the optimization techniques used in the paper may also relate to machine learning (cs.LG).
